This paper deals with the performance analysis of evolutionary algorithms, which is a topic closely related to the field of computational intelligence and optimization (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of noise in optimization, which is a topic relevant to data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.AI). The analysis of runtime bounds involves the study of algorithmic complexity, which is a topic in computer science theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents an example of a rugged landscape, which is a topic in the field of data structures (cs.DS).
